 contemporary nature of caste, conversion, religious synthesis, secularization, dalit politics, the inherent tensions of religious pluralism, and the struggle for recognition among subordinated people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCastexReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aChristianity and other religions. 0aChristianityzIndia, South. 0aSocial classeszIndia, SouthxReligious aspects. 0aTamil (Indic people)xReligion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  abooks for history lovers.  acaste system in india.  acatholicism.  achristian church.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  aevolution of christianity.  agod and religion.  ahinduism.  ahistory of christianity.  ahistory of religion.  ahome school history books.  aindian religion.  ainformative books.  aleisure reads.  anonfiction books.  apass on books.  apolitical.  areligion and culture.  areligion and politics.  areligion history and culture.  areligious studies.  asouth indian history.  awhat is christianity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095397040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953970423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953970/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles